article.headline: Cincinnati 77, S. Dakota 46
article.story: CINCINNATI -- Yancy Gates scored 16 points and had 11 rebounds and Deonta Vaughn added 12 points as Cincinnati easily beat South Dakota 77-46 Sunday night. Cincinnati (1-0) fell behind early but scored 17 straight points to move ahead 25-15. The Bearcats later used a 20-1 second half rally -- marked by Vaughn's 3-pointer and a dunk from Gates in his debut as a true freshman -- to put the game out of reach at 63-27. Cincinnati outrebounded South Dakota (0-2) 48-29 and held the Coyotes to just 30.5 percent shooting. Cincinnati made 48.4 percent of its shots. Louie Krogman and Dylan Grimsley each had 12 points for South Dakota. Tyler Cain added eight points and grabbed 12 rebounds. South Dakota, which lost to Cornell Friday night, is shifting to a Division I schedule this year after making the NCAA's Division II tournament each of the last five seasons.
